15) Pseudocode (Execution Flow)

for url in SOURCE_URLS:
    page = scrape(url)
    norm = normalize(page)
    if page_hash_unchanged(url, norm):
        continue

    blocks = segment(norm)
    chunks = build_chunks(blocks, size=650, overlap=100)
    chunks = enrich_metadata(chunks, url=url)
    changed_chunks = diff_against_active(chunks)

    # Stage E
    model = SentenceTransformer("BAAI/bge-large-en-v1.5")
    vectors = model.encode([c.text for c in changed_chunks],
                           batch_size=32, normalize_embeddings=True)
    save_embedding_records(changed_chunks, vectors)

    # Stage F — Chroma Cloud upsert
    client = chromadb.CloudClient(
        tenant=os.environ["CHROMA_TENANT"],
        database=os.environ["CHROMA_DATABASE"],
        api_key=os.environ["CHROMA_API_KEY"],
    )
    collection = client.get_or_create_collection("mutual_fund_chunks")
    collection.upsert(
        ids=[r["chunk_id"] for r in new_embedding_records],
        embeddings=[r["embedding_vector"] for r in new_embedding_records],
        documents=[r["text"] for r in new_embedding_records],
        metadatas=[{k: r[k] for k in ("source_url", "scheme_name", "section_name",
                    "field_type", "crawl_date", "content_hash",
                    "embedding_model", "embedded_at")}
                   for r in new_embedding_records],
    )

validate_collection(collection)   # 3-probe sanity retrieval

16) Non-Functional Targets

- Daily pipeline completion under 10 minutes for 7 URLs
- Incremental run should re-embed only changed pages
- Retrieval precision improvement for numeric fact queries versus naive fixed-split baseline
- Full audit trail for every chunk version and source mapping

This design provides a practical, production-oriented chunking and embedding architecture optimized for factual mutual fund Q&A with strict citation traceability.
Model pinned: BAAI/bge-large-en-v1.5 | Library: sentence-transformers | Dim: 1024 | Vector store: Chroma Cloud (https://www.trychroma.com)
